common, can you think of other examples?

27
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:19,130
>> So, it seems like we could talk a lot
about the physical arrangement of things

28
00:01:19,130 --> 00:01:20,390
in different types of rooms.

29
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:23,010
For example, when an airline
configures a new airplane they

30
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:25,600
have to configure the arrangement of the
seats, the arrangement of the window,

31
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:28,810
the arrangement of the emergency
exits and various things like that.

32
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:31,800
But I think configuration really goes
beyond just configuring the physical

33
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,330
layout of items.

34
00:01:33,330 --> 00:01:35,420
So, when I'm taking a picture with
my camera phone, for example,

35
00:01:35,420 --> 00:01:38,310
I have to configure different
options like the focus, whether or

36
00:01:38,310 --> 00:01:40,980
not the flash is on, my distance to
what I'm taking a picture of, and

37
00:01:40,980 --> 00:01:43,320
a few other different things like that.

38
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:45,580
In doing so I'm still balancing
different restrictions.

39
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:48,580
So, for example, if I'm taking a picture
of a landmark I can only be so

40
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:49,690
close to it.

41
00:01:49,690 --> 00:01:52,100
And therefore I might need to make
different decisions based on the focus

42
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:55,900
or the flash in order afford for
how far I can be from the landmark.

43
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:59,230
>> Design in general is a very common
information processing activity.

44
00:01:59,230 --> 00:02:02,040
And configuration is the most
common type of design.

